{
  "texts": [
    "Let ρ(x) be the ground state of H(x) and O be a sum of geometrically local observables with ∥O∥ ∞ ≤ 1.",
    "We assume that the geometry of the n-qubit system is known, but we do not know how h j ð x!",
    "j Þ is parameterized or what the observable O is.",
    "The goal is to learn a function h * (x) that approximates the ground state property TrðOρðxÞÞ from a classical dataset,",
    "where y ' ≈ TrðOρðx ' ÞÞ records the ground state property for x ℓ ∈ [-1, 1] m sampled from an arbitrary unknown distribution D. Here, y ' ≈ TrðOρðx ' ÞÞ means that y ℓ has additive error at most ϵ."
  ]
}